1

00:00:02,600  -->  00:00:04,735
Before we get started,

2

00:00:04,735  -->  00:00:07,680
let's take a step back and look at the big picture of

3

00:00:07,680  -->  00:00:11,170
what machine learning is and how aggression fits into it.

4

00:00:11,170  -->  00:00:15,075
You might have heard of machine learning as it's currently a really hot topic,

5

00:00:15,075  -->  00:00:17,385
but the truth is that it isn't really new.

6

00:00:17,385  -->  00:00:22,085
It's just a new way to package things that have actually existed for a really long time.

7

00:00:22,085  -->  00:00:24,540
Two primary branches of machine learning are called

8

00:00:24,540  -->  00:00:27,495
supervised learning and unsupervised learning.

9

00:00:27,495  -->  00:00:32,850
Supervised learning is where we use input data to predict a label for that data.

10

00:00:32,850  -->  00:00:35,250
Examples of this type of machine learning are using

11

00:00:35,250  -->  00:00:39,135
credit card transaction data to predict fraudulent transactions,

12

00:00:39,135  -->  00:00:44,055
or using customer financial data to predict the chance of a default on a loan,

13

00:00:44,055  -->  00:00:48,090
or using neighborhood characteristics to predict home prices.

14

00:00:48,090  -->  00:00:52,920
Another large branch of machine learning is known as unsupervised machine learning.

15

00:00:52,920  -->  00:00:54,375
In this type of machine learning,

16

00:00:54,375  -->  00:00:57,935
you're clustering together data based on common characteristics.

17

00:00:57,935  -->  00:01:01,575
These data don't have labels like in supervised machine learning techniques.

18

00:01:01,575  -->  00:01:06,480
Common unsupervised problems include trying to group similar customer segments,

19

00:01:06,480  -->  00:01:09,480
or group documents that cover similar topics.

20

00:01:09,480  -->  00:01:13,555
There are other machine learning approaches but these are the two main branches.

21

00:01:13,555  -->  00:01:14,940
And as it turns out,

22

00:01:14,940  -->  00:01:19,810
linear and logistic regression fall into the supervised machine learning branch.
